post_text:
The City of Fullerton is hosting a COVID-19 Emergency Rental Assistance Program Event at the Fullerton Community Center this Friday, September 11th from 8am to 2pm. No RSVP needed, walk-ins are welcome.
The COVID-19 Rental Assistance Program will provide a one-time emergency rental assistance to Fullerton residents facing financial hardship due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Eligible households can receive a one-time grant up to $1,000.
Please visit cityoffullerton.com/rentalassistance to view the application and program requirements. Attendees should bring and complete all required documentation prior to the event. Questions? Please call 714-738-6544.

The FSD Regular Board Meeting on September 8, 2020, will begin at 6:00 p.m. (Open Session) and will be held in person by the Board of Trustees. There will be no Zoom or livestream available. Attendees at the Board Meeting will adhere to physical distancing, wear a face covering (mask) and their temperature will be taken.

Public comment may be submitted by email to publiccomment@myfsd.org on or before Tuesday, September 8, 2020 at 2:30 p.m. and include first and last name of person submitting public comment. Please limit comments to 450 words or less to address the Board on each agenda or non-agenda item. An email for public comment must be submitted by specific agenda item or topic and not combined.

post_text: We appreciate all the input and comments we received about the photographs on possible school opening scenarios and will be incorporating some of the input we have received. Guidance from our State and local educational and health agencies continues to evolve at a fast pace. At FSD we are continuing to work together to best plan for our students, teachers, staff, and families. We are exploring different options for a safe return to school in accordance with those guidelines. We are in unprecedented times and realize that the needs for every family differ. In response, staff is working hard to offer options for our families when school starts on August 11 and to plan early so as not to be caught unprepared. We realize that no plan will suit everyone's needs and this is a fluid situation that requires adjustments. We look forward to our continued partnership with staff and families to provide input and finalize the different methods and practices of returning to school that may be best for your family. Thank you for your patience and understanding.

post_text: Throwback Thursday to our visit to the inclusive environments at Woodcrest Elementary! Woodcrest teachers plan lessons where their 4th grade students work with students with special needs to help create relationships and strengthen the inclusive environment that Woodcrest nurtures. In these photos, teacher Susie Wren's 4th grade students are working with SDC (Special Day Class) students from Ms. Samosa's class on an art project, where they create a portrait using a collage technique, where only one photo is from a photo of them, and the rest of the images are from different people. The message is one of empathy and understanding, and though we may look different, we can find unity. The students were great, and we loved seeing the inclusive environment, where Mrs. Wren's students were reaching out and helping the SDC students through the steps of the art project. Woodcrest teacher Ms. Pionke also participates with her class. A truly beautiful sight to see.

Fullerton School District
May 28 at 5:35 PM Â·

Attention Incoming Kindergarteners! Come to our Dual Language Academy at Pacific Drive! If you are interested in enrolling in this program, call (714) 447-7416, email fullerton_dla@myfsd.org, or visit https://bit.ly/FullertonDLA.

Do you have an incoming Kindergarten student for the 2020-2021 school year?

Are you interested in your child becoming bilingual and bi-literate in Spanish and English?

The Fullerton School District is currently seeking incoming kindergarten students to register for Pacific Driveâs Dual Language Academy or (DLA).

Pacific Drive has been recognized at the local and state level for implementing a variety of programs that support students academically, socially, and create a safe learning environment.

In a kindergarten classroom where Spanish is spoken 90% of the time, our students develop a love of reading!

Our Dual Language Academy not only supports language development but also implements the most cutting edge, research-based instructional strategies including cognitive guided instruction for math and Writers workshop
